<item>
            <title>[HBASE-15266] add precommit check for &quot;catch Throwable&quot;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-15266</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Catching Throwable is usually incorrect because it gets all of the Error derived problems, like ThreadDeath, OutOfMemoryError, VM malfunctions, linker problems, etc.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I was surprised to see findbugs did not flag catching throwable in the patches on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-9393&quot; title=&quot;Hbase does not closing a closed socket resulting in many CLOSE_WAIT &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-9393&quot;&gt;HBASE-9393&lt;/a&gt;. We should add a precommit check that looks expressly for it, in our &quot;hbase antipatterns&quot; test plugin.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
